Text.Value: I thought so too - but I found nothing. And regretted everything.
If you can tell right from wrong, maybe we can still fix this.
Why would you do something like that?
I can't, I can't. It's too late.
No. I thought there might be more to take. Hidden inside.
Who are you talking about?
They gave me what they had. Should I have let them leave?
Leave.
My guilt is my payment. My debts, bottomless.
Perhaps you'd feel less guilty if you paid for your crimes too.
Yes - yes yes. Help me. Make me pay.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The visage is excited by the prospect of finally being freed of its guilt (by being killed)

Text.Value: Smart - the most precious things are often hidden deepest.
People die all the time. Stop being dramatic, and get over it.
They paid a different price in the end.
They paid more than their share.
Yes, yes. I have gold. So much gold. Take it.
That's what I thought. But I found nothing.
No - there's always more to take.
Some wouldn't pay their dues. Some couldn't.

EditorData.NodeContext: Rising disgust with each sentence - but a twinge of malice with the last few words

Text.Value: Yes. Many died - all for trying to pass. I took too much from them.
I opened them. Searched inside them.
That sounds like it might have proved fatal.

EditorData.stateContext: The Visage of Guilt is a floating head

Text.Value: So many. Too many.
Yes. But I guess you didn't.
Take it all, whatever the cost.

Synopsis: The Visage of Guilt, hovering in front of several skeletons (dead adventurers that found their end by the hands of the Tollhouse Collector).
